criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Children from 8 to 12 years of age;

          -  At least one first permanent or incisive erupted incisor (with occlusal / incisal
             surface free of gingiva) present in the oral cavity;

          -  Teeth presenting hypomineralization lesions sensitive.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Children with enamel malformations linked to syndromes, with dental fluorosis, enamel
             hypoplasia or with imperfect amelogenesis;

          -  Teeth with loss of dental structure and carious lesion;

          -  Children in orthodontic treatment;

          -  Children with cognition problems;

          -  Children who used any type of analgesic / anti-inflammatory medication before
             treatment;

          -  Children undergoing desensitizing treatment in the last 3 months

          -  Children with behavioral problems;

          -  Children with occlusal problems such as tightening and bruxism.
